<br>
I really feel as though casting &quot;instruction&quot; is one of my major weaknesses on the test. Just because I have a passion for it doesn't mean I'm good at it. Jeffery Barefoot also published a lesson plan that I may ask him to post here as well. Your MOI goes into great detail on how a student understands the material which I don't think anyone else out there is doing. I have no interest in a casting school being the &quot;John Wilson Show&quot;. The really cool comments I get are when someone tells me that a particular tip or comment &quot;revolutionized&quot; their casting. That really indicates some understanding of the material.<br>
<br>
By the way I had one of those types of epiphany from reading your MOI.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
