John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flysoup>flysoup</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#000000>(12/20/03 11:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lesson</span><hr size=1>  Howdy Mike,<br>
 The points you brought up are very good. A good formate is needed to develop a good course.<br>
 I feel that what I needed might have been more long the lines of what Jeffery offered in his lesson plan.<br>
 I have been a teacher of fly casting since the mid 60's This and other boards have congealed the wording and are making the teaching of  Fly Casting a better thought out program. With out the FFF we would be each trying to reinvent a way to teach. Having people that are willing to offer some insight in to the teaching is the way we should strive to do. <br>
 One thing that Floyd brought to light for me was to To have the Student reach I &quot;Higher Standard&quot; I like the way that sounds. The Intermediate caster is held to a higher standard in his personal casting.<br>
 This is good instruction and teaching.<br>
Thanks Mike for the syllabus.<br>
 ol Al  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jimmyt@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Jimmy T</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 502<br> <font color=#000000>(1/7/04 8:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lesson</span><hr size=1> A good learning system.  Reminds me a lot of the days when I was learning sales 20 some odd years ago.  Very comprehensive technique set out in a definitave format that allows the teacher space but keeps the lesson on plan...<br>
Wished I'd had a plan as well thought out then as you lay out now.<br>
<br>
I would say it's good format for teaching just about anything.<br>
More than anything mike it has reminded me that I am a teacher and to focus on the learning from the perspective of the student or learnee....<br>
<br>
Jimmy T.<br>
